== Roasted Potatoes ==

Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash
and dry all produce.

Dice @Yukon Gold potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces; toss on a #baking sheet{}
with a drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack, tossing halfway through, until browned and tender,
~{20-25%minutes}.

== Lemony Green Beans ==

Meanwhile, trim @green beans{6%ounce}, if necessary. Halve, peel, and mince
@red onion{1/2}(peeled and minced) (whole onion for 4 servings). Strip
@rosemary{1%tsp} leaves from stems (2 tsp for 4); finely chop leaves.
Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

Toss green beans on a second baking sheet with a drizzle of oil, salt, and
pepper.

Roast on middle rack until browned and tender, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Save lemon zest for later.

== Chicken with Balsamic Fig Sauce ==

While green beans roast, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{};
season all over with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and
cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Transfer to a #cutting board{} and set aside to rest.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} in pan used for chicken over medium heat.
Add minced onion and chopped rosemary. Cook, stirring, until softened,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in @balsamic vinegar{5%tsp} and @fig jam{1}. Simmer until syrupy,
~{30-60%seconds}.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1} and @water{¼%cup} (1/3 cup for 4 servings).
Cook until thick and glossy, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add a splash of water if sauce is
too thick.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if sauce is too thick.

Remove pan from heat and stir in @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4) until melted.
Season with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Once green beans are done, carefully toss with lemon zest.

Thinly slice chicken crosswise.

Divide chicken, potatoes, and green beans between plates. Drizzle chicken with
sauce. Serve with lemon wedges on the side.